{
  "texts": [
    "C. Lemma: Axis-Aligned Scaling is Rarely OptimalLemma 1.",
    "If ∂F ∂H ̸ = 0 and ∂F ∂∥V ∥ ̸ = 0, then the optimal direction is neither horizontal nor vertical.Proof Sketch.",
    "If optimal scaling were horizontal, direction vector would be (1, 0).",
    "But:∇F • (1, 0) = ∂F ∂H ̸ = 0, contradiction.Similarly for vertical scaling.",
    "Thus diagonal scaling is required."
  ]
}